<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_48b824c2-dc86-40a7-b51b-f6336c76450b" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>B6P1</sptc><title id="_5607ab2c-a00d-4ed2-8431-4a0251bc514f">Pressure</title><archive-num>2019: BP6.2</archive-num><subclause id="_bebfcde6-2507-4bbb-ae5f-2fabb6d4ad3f" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_a0e03b29-b105-47c8-8034-8f62ae12fdc1">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The points of discharge of a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1422_4.4.0.xml#_bd764954-3054-4109-81f2-164feefc5058" id="_e32aa0ec-505e-4862-bb53-771c7554cf49" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">rainwater service</xref> must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_2fdb8f74-5519-4d8d-811d-75f8026b7ca2">have—<ol><li>a working pressure of not less than 50 kPa; and</li><li>a static pressure within a building of not more than 500 kPa; or</li></ol></li><li id="_da1a94f8-945a-42e0-b011-84d16272e74e">have water pressures suitable for the correct functioning of the fixture or appliance where water pressures outside of (a)(i) and (a)(ii) are required.</li></ol></subclause></clause>